    "problemStatement": "You are given three positive integers NNN, MMM and KKK.\n\nAn array of integers A1,A2,\u2026,ANA_1, A_2, \\dots, A_NA1\u200b,A2\u200b,\u2026,AN\u200b is good if the following statements hold:\n\n\n0\u2264Ai\u2264M0 \\leq A_i \\leq M0\u2264Ai\u200b\u2264M for each (1\u2264i\u2264N1 \\leq i \\leq N1\u2264i\u2264N)\n(Ai\u2005\u200a&amp;\u2005\u200aK)\u2264(Ai+1\u2005\u200a&amp;\u2005\u200aK)(A_i \\; \\&amp; \\; K) \\leq (A_{i+1} \\; \\&amp; \\; K)(Ai\u200b&amp;K)\u2264(Ai+1\u200b&amp;K) for each (1\u2264i\u2264N\u221211 \\leq i \\leq N-11\u2264i\u2264N\u22121)\n(Ai\u2005\u200a\u2223\u2005\u200aK)\u2264(Ai+1\u2005\u200a\u2223\u2005\u200aK)(A_i \\; | \\; K) \\leq (A_{i+1} \\; | \\; K)(Ai\u200b\u2223K)\u2264(Ai+1\u200b\u2223K) for each (1\u2264i\u2264N\u221211 \\leq i \\leq N-11\u2264i\u2264N\u22121)\nHere, &amp;\\&amp;&amp; denotes the bitwise AND operation and \u2223|\u2223 denotes the bitwise OR operation.\n\nCount the number of good arrays A1,A2,\u2026,ANA_1, A_2, \\dots, A_NA1\u200b,A2\u200b,\u2026,AN\u200b. As the result can be very large, you should print it modulo 998\u2009244\u2009353998\\,244\\,353998244353.\n\n\nInput Format\n\nThe first line contains TTT, the number of testcases. Then the testcases follow.\nThe only line of each test case contains three integers NNN, MMM, KKK.\n\n\nOutput Format\nFor each test case, print a single integer: the number of good arrays, modulo 998\u2009244\u2009353998\\,244\\,353998244353.",
    "constraints": [
      "1\u2264T\u22642\u22c51051 \\leq T \\leq 2 \\cdot 10^51\u2264T\u22642\u22c5105",
      "1\u2264N&lt;2201 \\le N \\lt 2^{20}1\u2264N&lt;220",
